    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require all police forces to review serious cold cases within 5\u201310 years",
        "additional_details": "Support \u2018Stacey\u2019s Law\u2019 so no victim is forgotten and no other family waits 33 years for justice\r\n\r\nFamilies can wait decades for justice while evidence degrades and witnesses are lost. With no national rule, we\u2019re concerned that reviews depend on funding and location, creating a postcode lottery.\r\nPolice and Crime Commissioners who currently decide will soon leave post due to government changes, we believe now is the time to act.\r\n\u2018Stacey\u2019s Law\u2019 would ensure timely, fair reviews and protect every victim\u2019s chance of justice.\u201d",
        "background": "Require all police forces in England and Wales to review serious cold cases within 5\u201310 years. This should be called 'Stacey\u2019s Law\u2019.\r\n\r\nEnd the postcode lottery, protect vital evidence, give families a fair, timely chance at justice.",
